140 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
INTERPRETING ELECTION RESULTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I wondered what explanations the fundamental liberal media elitists would 
conjure up to save face after yet another attempt to brainwash the public into 
thinking that a handful of "religious extremists" was all that was backing 
passage of the repeal of special rights ordinances in Irvine, Concord and San 
Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
I thought the excuse for San Francisco was original: the earthquake. And I also 
heard someone on a San Francisco talk show say that in off-year elections, 
there's a more conservative turnout. I guess you could use that alibi for the 
Irvine and Concord results as well. I have an explanation of my own. How about 
this: The majority of voters in these cities (and they can't all be "religious 
extremists") did not want the unequal special rights ordinances forced on them 
by a few politicians. 
</P>
<P>
BRENDA HESTER 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA112289-0010 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 138184 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
November 22, 1989, Wednesday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
