<HEADLINE>
<P>
MATTER OF BELIEFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On the front page (Nov.17) were the following two headlines: "Six Jesuit 
Priests Slain in Salvador" and "Pro-Choice Lawmaker Is Barred From Church 
Rite." I'm sure I'm not the only person to notice the incredible irony of the 
situation. 
</P>
<P>
On one hand, we see dedicated Jesuit priests willing to die for their beliefs, 
one of which is their concept of freedom. On the other hand, we have a priest 
withholding a sacrament because an elected official has used her freedom to 
disagree with the church. What's wrong with this picture? 
</P>
<P>
KATHYRN J. TAIT 
</P>
<P>
Yorba Linda 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
