<HEADLINE>
<P>
MURRAY LEADS UCLA OVER AUSSIES, 80-68 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JERRY CROWE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Freshman Tracy Murray scored 16 points and pulled down six rebounds to lead 
UCLA to an 80-68 exhibition victory over the Australian National Team Tuesday 
night in front of 5,341 at Pauley Pavilion. 
</P>
<P>
The Aussies found themselves down under in a hurry, giving up 27 consecutive 
points and missing 14 shots in a row after taking a 2-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
But they closed to within 55-49 midway through the second half as guard Philip 
Smyth made four three-point shots. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA's three freshmen -- Murray, Zan Mason and Mitchell Butler -- then scored 
all but one of the Bruins' next 17 points as they pulled away in their final 
tuneup before Saturday night's regular-season opener against Santa Clara. JERRY 
CROWE 
</P>
