<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
ANTELOPE VALLEY BASKETBALL TEAM SUFFERS 1ST LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Freshman forward Joe Mantashigian came off the bench to score a team-high 22 
points Tuesday, but that was not enough to help Antelope Valley College as the 
Marauders fell to College of the Sequoias, 88-77, in a nonconference game in 
Visalia. 
</P>
<P>
It was the first loss of the season for Antelope Valley (3-1). 
</P>
<P>
Danny Griffin had 14 points, and Dedan Thomas and Paul Ernst each scored 11 
points for Antelope Valley. 
</P>
<P>
Sequoias improved its record to 4-2. 
