<HEADLINE>
<P>
KILLER OF PREGNANT DOCTOR GETS MAXIMUM TERM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A former mental patient apologized for attacking and killing a pregnant 
physician before a judge sentenced him to prison for 50 years to life, the 
maximum penalty for the crimes. 
</P>
<P>
Steven Smith, 23, was sentenced Monday for the rape, sodomy, robbery and murder 
of Dr. Kathryn Hinnant, 33, in her Bellvue Hospital office in January. Smith 
had pleaded insanity. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm sorry and it shouldn't have happened," Smith said at the sentencing. 
"There was a lot of things going on that I didn't see or feel, or anything like 
that." 
</P>
</TEXT>
