<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: WASTE INCINERATOR BUILDER SUES AIR QUALITY 
DISTRICT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A company seeking to build a hazardous waste incinerator in Vernon sued the 
South Coast Air Quality Management District Tuesday, claiming the agency 
unfairly required new environmental studies before renewing its building 
permits. 
</P>
<P>
Security Environmental Systems Inc. charged in its federal suit that the AQMD 
denied it its due process rights by forcing it to meet the newly imposed 
environmental reporting requirements after it had already met previous 
requirements. 
</P>
<P>
The company said the conditions imposed this year on its second request since 
1987 to win AQMD extensions on 21 building permits were tantamount to a 
revocation of all the permits it had sought from governments and regulators 
since it began the project in 1985. 
</P>
