<HEADLINE>
<P>
HEROES IN 'STALKER' CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles County Board of Supervisors on Tuesday divided shares of a 
$36,777.63 reward bounty for the capture of convicted "Night Stalker" Richard 
Ramirez. Nineteen awards were paid out in amounts ranging from $250 to 
$10,388.82. Here are the reward amounts and the roles the recipients played. 
</P>
<P>
 * $10,388.82 -- Provided investigators with Ramirez's name, facts about the 
crimes, and assisted in recovery of one of the murder weapons. 
</P>
<P>
* $6,388.81 -- Provided information regarding Ramirez's name and assisted 
investigators in recovering stolen property taken from homes of murder victims. 
</P>
<P>
* $3,250 -- Called homicide detectives on behalf of her father and persuaded 
her father to come forward with information. 
</P>
<P>
* $2,500 -- Gave information leading to Ramirez's true name. 
</P>
<P>
* $2,500 -- Persuaded her brother and his wife to come forward and provide 
information to the Lompoc Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
* $1,000 -- Supplied the partial license plate number of a stolen vehicle that 
Ramirez used in an Orange County attempted murder. 
</P>
<P>
* $1,000 -- Provided the entire license plate number of the vehicle used in the 
Orange County attempted murder. 
</P>
<P>
* $1,000 -- Followed Ramirez as he was attempting to evade arrest and directed 
another person to call the Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
* $1,000 -- Amount for each of three people who physically detained Ramirez the 
day of his arrest. 
</P>
<P>
* $1,000 -- Assisted in the arrest of Ramirez by physically restraining him. 
</P>
<P>
* $1,000 -- Amount for each of three people who assisted in physically subduing 
Ramirez. 
</P>
<P>
* $500 -- Called 911 at the direction of a claimant, notifying the Sheriff's 
Department of Ramirez's location. 
</P>
<P>
* $500 -- Amount for each of two people who called 911, directing officers to 
Ramirez's location the day of his arrest. 
</P>
<P>
* $250 -- Furnished information to the San Francisco Police Department 
regarding Ramirez and stolen property. 
</P>
</TEXT>
