<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 2 BADLY INJURED WHEN CAR DRIFTS OFF FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three members of a family from San Bernardino County were injured, two 
seriously, early Tuesday when the car in which they were riding veered off the 
Golden State Freeway north of Los Angeles and flipped over, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver, Katherine Aguirre, 21, and passenger Brandon Aguirre, 1, were 
thrown from the car in the 4 a.m. crash near Gorman, said California Highway 
Patrol Officer Mark Ehly. Passenger Bryan Aguirre, 26, was not ejected, Ehly 
said. 
</P>
<P>
All three were taken to Henry Mayo Memorial Hospital in Newhall, where 
Katherine Aguirre was listed in critical condition and Brandon Aguirre was in 
stable condition, Ehly said. Bryan Aguirre received only minor injuries. The 
family lives in Bloomington. 
</P>
<P>
The three were traveling north near Hungry Valley Road when the car drifted off 
the freeway and down an embankment, Ehly said. 
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident had not been determined, he said. 
</P>
