<TEXT>
<P>
Kent C. (Oz) Nelson has been elected chairman and chief executive of United 
Parcel Service, which has headquarters in Greenwich, Conn. Nelson, 52, who had 
been vice chairman since February, succeeds John W. (Jack) Rogers. Rogers, the 
UPS chairman and CEO since 1984, will continue to serve as a director and 
chairman of the executive committee. 
</P>
