BUSH THANKSGIVING ADDRESS ON RADIO, TV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush will address the nation in a live broadcast airing tonight at 6 
on ABC, CBS, NBC and cable's CNN. 
</P>
<P>
The Thanksgiving speech, originating from Camp David, will express gratitude 
for the nation's bounty and for democratic reforms taking place in Eastern 
Europe. 
</P>
<P>
On radio, the speech can be heard on KFWB (980), KNX (1070) and KCRW-FM (89.9). 
</P>
<P>
The networks also may preempt regular programming to cover the scheduled 4:30 
p.m. launch of the space shuttle Discovery. 
</P>
