<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
VICTIM IDENTIFIED IN FATAL SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police Tuesday identified a man Tuesday who staggered several blocks before 
dropping dead of a bullet wound Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
The body of Robert Joseph Herrera, 23, of Placentia was found by officers in 
the 200 block of North Clementine Street. Witnesses told police that they heard 
gunshots but did not see the attack about 8 p.m. Monday in the 300 block of 
West Chartres Street. There was no motive or description of the shooter, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
It was the second fatal shooting in the area recently. On Nov. 7, the body of a 
35-year-old man was found with a gunshot wound to the head in a car on the 
north side of Pearson Park, at Sycamore Street and Harbor Boulevard, Anaheim 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
Since no weapon was found nearby, the latest case was being handled as a 
homicide. But police said they had no suspects or motives for the shooting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
