<P>
DAY-CARE CENTER ADDING 30 SPOTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A day-care center run by the Assistance League of Santa Ana has been expanded 
from 70 to 100 children, according to the center. 
</P>
<P>
The center, at 1002 W. 2nd St., is open from 6:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. It accepts 
children from 2 to 5 years old and provides breakfast and snacks. Tuition is on 
a sliding scale up to $80 per week. The center accepts children who are not 
toilet-trained. 
