<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: WORKPLACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Leslie Berkman, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Desperately Seeking Nannies: A company that specializes in recruiting 
"All-American" nannies from small Midwest and Northwest towns opened two months 
ago in El Toro and already has more requests for nannies than it can readily 
fill, owner Anne Leets said. 
</P>
<P>
"Child care is a big issue for working parents," said Leets, the founder of 
All-American Childcare Agency. 
</P>
<P>
She said the live-in nannies she places accept salaries at the going rate in 
Southern California, ranging from $150 to $250 a week plus room and board. But 
she said the family employer also must pay for transportation to bring them 
from their home towns. 
</P>
<P>
Leets said that since she founded her agency in September, she has placed close 
to 30 nannies throughout Orange County. "Right now I have three clients for 
every nanny I can find," she said. 
</P>
