<P>
PRINCIPAL 'REHEARSED' IN DARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Victoria Principal prepared for her role as a blind woman in a Sunday 
made-for-television movie by wearing a blindfold for two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
"I cooked dinner blindfolded, I baked, I made sandwiches, I scrambled eggs, ate 
meals, and I even tended to business at my office with my eyes covered," said 
the former star of CBS's "Dallas" in an interview with TV Guide. 
</P>
<P>
In the ABC movie "Blind Witness," Principal plays a determined blind woman who 
avenges her husband's murder. During filming in Utah, she wore special contact 
lenses that distorted her vision and made her legally blind. 
</P>
<P>
"I had to memorize all my locations before we shot a scene," said Principal, 
who was also executive producer for the movie. "I would count every step and 
practice moving to my marks over and over again because I couldn't see my 
marks." 
</P>
