<HEADLINE>
<P>
NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
MR. T'S BROTHER SHOOTS ROBBER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An off-duty police officer, the brother and former bodyguard of television star 
Mr. T, shot and wounded a man who tried to rob him at a South Side currency 
exchange, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The officer, Gustave J. Tero, a patrolman assigned to the Police Training 
Academy, was waiting to cash his paycheck Tuesday when two men tried to rob 
him, police said. Tero's brother, Lawrence (Mr. T) Tero, played a tough law 
enforcer with a trademark shaved head in television's "The A Team." 
</P>
<P>
Tero struggled with the two robbers and chased one of them into a nearby alley, 
Cmdr. Toby Burton said. Tero struggled with the man again and shot him in the 
legs, Burton said. 
</P>
<P>
The second robber and a getaway driver fled and are still at large, Burton 
said. The wounded man was hospitalized in fair condition. The police 
department's Office of Professional Standards is investigating the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
Gustave Tero had once served as a bodyguard for Lawrence but was fired after a 
year. He sued his brother in 1984 to recoup $72,000 in damages and salary he 
claimed he lost for taking a year off from the department. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
