<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEHAVIOR NETS 76ER BARKLEY $5,000 FINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Charles Barkley, the Philadelphia 76ers' high-scoring forward, has been fined 
$5,000 by the NBA for his conduct during a game against the Orlando Magic, the 
league said today. 
</P>
<P>
Barkley was fined for "verbal abuse of a referee and failing to leave the court 
in a timely fashion after he had been ejected from the game," Rod Thorn, NBA 
vice president of operations, said. 
</P>
<P>
Barkley was ejected after being called for his second technical foul, with 32 
seconds remaining in Saturday night's 116-103 Orlando victory over 
Philadelphia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
